Preconditions:
- The input array `parent` is not null.
- The input string `s` is not null.
- The length of `parent` is equal to the length of `s`.
- The length of `parent` is greater than or equal to 1.
- The value of `parent[0]` is -1.
- The values in `parent` are within the range of 0 to n-1.
- The input string `s` consists of only lowercase English letters.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the length of the longest path in the tree.
- The longest path in the tree has no pair of adjacent nodes with the same character assigned to them.
- The length of the longest path is greater than or equal to 0.
- The length of the longest path is less than or equal to the number of nodes in the tree.